using UnityEngine;

public class ChallengeError : MonoBehaviour
{
    void OnTriggerEnter2D(Collider2D other)
    {
        // Forgetting to check tags
        // This will try to destroy everything that touches it!
        Destroy(other.gameObject);  // Destroys the player too!
    }
}

phase2.explanation:
Without checking tags, the trigger destroys anything that enters it — including the player.

**The fix:**
```csharp
void OnTriggerEnter2D(Collider2D other)
{
    if (other.CompareTag("Coin"))
    {
        Destroy(other.gameObject);
    }
    // Player is safe!
}
```

**Sharp-chan says:**
"Always check tags before destroying objects. Otherwise, you'll destroy things you didn't mean to."
